snippet.textDisplay:
As someone who has a pretty weird and difficult relationship with my father, despite all the love, this song always makes me cry.

We truly love each other. We can chat, joke and work together. But we're so stubborn and so equal that it get hard sometimes. Especially during my teens... now, I'm married and about to buy my house and he is one of my best friends. We still fight? A lot. Still hurts? Yeap.

But I know that I love him. And I know how much he loves me.
And damn, watch her family videos was a ride... I remember all the videos and photos we have, all the adoration in his eyes looking at me... that photos while I still fit into one arm. And I promised myself that I wouldn't settle for someone that didn't look at me like that - or couldn't look to our kids like that.
